cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DC

The paper focuses on the scientometric evaluation of faculty members in Greek Science and Engineering University Departments, which involves the collection and analysis of data on the number of papers, citations, h-index, and i10-index. This falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR), as well as cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the use of Google Scholar and Publish or Perish for data collection and analysis. Additionally, the evaluation of departments and scholars could also fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it involves analyzing large amounts of data.
